00:43:15,400 --> 00:43:21,720
of you. I want you to write and publish something 
every month." I was like, "What are you talking  

542
00:43:21,720 --> 00:43:27,120
about? Why would you say that?" He said, "You 
have so much to teach people. Just do it."  

543
00:43:27,720 --> 00:43:31,840
I said, "I don't really have that much to say." 
And he's like, "Just trust me on this. You'll  

544
00:43:31,840 --> 00:43:36,400
figure it out." His advice was write what you 
repeat. If you say something more than once,  

545
00:43:36,400 --> 00:43:40,720
just write it down. And then the next time 
someone asks you, you can just hand them. 

546
00:43:40,720 --> 00:43:45,240
He has a great blog if you have read it. I just 
normally thinking that is a weird thing for your  

547
00:43:45,240 --> 00:43:51,320
new manager to say after you had a lot of conflict 
together before that. But he took my contract,  

548
00:43:51,320 --> 00:43:54,280
which was... By the way, he's like, "Oh, do 
you want to codify this in some way?" I'm like,  

549
00:43:54,280 --> 00:43:58,160
"No, I just..." But every month from then 
on, I would literally just write something  

550
00:43:58,160 --> 00:44:02,920
and it was my promise to him. And I did it 
faithfully and I published it internally. So  

551
00:44:02,920 --> 00:44:05,760
I didn't publish it externally for a long time.
And then sometimes they would ask me if I want  

552
00:44:05,760 --> 00:44:09,320
to publish it externally for the company 
and I would say yes. And so I did it for  

553
00:44:09,320 --> 00:44:13,600
years. I reported to him for years. And then we 
switched managers. He moved over to Reality Labs  

554
00:44:13,600 --> 00:44:20,080
and then I had a new manager and I continued and 
I continued this. Then I started doing a publicly,  

555
00:44:20,080 --> 00:44:24,840
and then obviously I wrote a book. 
Because of him and his encouragement,  

556
00:44:24,840 --> 00:44:29,200
it got me to a totally different place. And 
part of it was just the commitment. I now had  

557
00:44:29,200 --> 00:44:32,760
accountability because I knew he was watching. 
I'm not actually sure if he was actually watching  

558
00:44:32,760 --> 00:44:37,800
every month. But I felt the accountability to do 
this and I've done it every single month since.

559
00:44:37,800 --> 00:44:41,760
So it's interesting that that's another 
example of your manager giving you the  

560
00:44:41,760 --> 00:44:48,520
space slash forcing you to share publicly being a 
